# KPI Evolution by Agency Stage

Understanding how the same KPIs mean different things—and serve different purposes—as agencies mature through the Agency Evolution Ladder.

## Core Principle

**The metrics don't change — the meaning does.**

The same 10-12 KPIs form the skeleton of every healthy agency, but as you climb the AE Ladder, you start reading them through different lenses:
- **Rising:** Survival and rhythm
- **Striving:** Efficiency and control
- **Thriving:** Predictability and leadership leverage
- **Driving:** Optionality and enterprise value

---

## The Agency Evolution Ladder Context

### Stage Definitions

| Stage | Revenue Range | Primary Focus | Leadership Mode |
|-------|--------------|---------------|-----------------|
| **Rising** | ≤$1.5M AGI | Stabilize & Earn | Practitioner-Manager |
| **Striving** | $1.5M-3M AGI | Systemize & Control | Manager-CEO |
| **Thriving** | $3M-7M AGI | Scale & Predict | CEO |
| **Driving** | $7M-15M+ AGI | Optimize & Capitalize | CEO-Advisor |

---

## Financial Performance KPIs: Evolution by Stage

### AGI (Agency Gross Income)

| Stage | Focus | Question Answered | Success Metric | Common Issue |
|-------|-------|-------------------|----------------|--------------|
| **Rising** | Build consistent monthly AGI | "Can we make money every month?" | Positive AGI 10+ months/year | Revenue volatility |
| **Striving** | Improve AGI quality (reduce pass-throughs) | "Can we keep what we earn?" | 80-90% AGI% | Pass-through dependency |
| **Thriving** | Diversify AGI streams | "Can we scale predictably?" | 85-92% AGI%, multiple revenue streams | Service concentration risk |
| **Driving** | Optimize AGI yield per account | "Can we scale profitably at volume?" | 90-95% AGI%, high-value client mix | Maintaining quality at scale |

**Interpretation Evolution:**

**Rising:** "Did we hit our number?"
- Simple top-line focus
- Success = consistent revenue
- Volatility acceptable

**Striving:** "How much of revenue do we actually keep?"
- Understanding pass-through impact
- Success = improving AGI%
- Quality focus emerging

**Thriving:** "Is our revenue model scalable?"
- Service mix optimization
- Success = predictable, high-quality AGI
- Diversification important

**Driving:** "Are we maximizing client value?"
- Premium positioning
- Success = exceptional AGI% with volume
- Enterprise-grade operations

---

### EBITDA Margin

| Stage | Target Range | Purpose | Decision Enabled | Investment Focus |
|-------|-------------|---------|------------------|------------------|
| **Rising** | 10-25% | Survival to stability | Can we pay ourselves? | Minimal—focus on revenue |
| **Striving** | 20-30% | Margin control discipline | Can we reinvest? | Process improvement |
| **Thriving** | 30-35% | Strong profitability | Can we scale? | Leadership & systems |
| **Driving** | 35-45% | Enterprise-grade margins | Can we optimize valuation? | Technology & innovation |

**Interpretation Evolution:**

**Rising:** "Are we profitable enough to survive?"
- Breaking even → 10% feels like victory
- Any profit is progress
- Focus: Don't go negative

**Striving:** "Are our margins healthy enough to grow?"
- 20-30% becomes target
- Reinvestment capacity matters
- Focus: Protect margins while scaling

**Thriving:** "Are we as efficient as we should be?"
- 30-35% expected
- Benchmark against best-in-class
- Focus: Optimize without sacrificing quality

**Driving:** "Can we demonstrate enterprise value?"
- 35-45% creates acquisition premium
- Margin stability valued highly
- Focus: Sustain margins at scale

---

### AGI per FTE

| Stage | Target Range | Meaning | Hiring Philosophy | Risk to Monitor |
|-------|-------------|---------|-------------------|-----------------|
| **Rising** | $140K-160K | Learning workload balance | Hiring ahead acceptable | Overcapacity |
| **Striving** | $160K-180K | Establishing efficiency | Balance growth & margin | Over-hiring |
| **Thriving** | $180K-200K | Predictable leverage | Forecast-driven hiring | Under-investment |
| **Driving** | $200K-225K+ | Sustainable plateau | Strategic capacity | Over-leverage |

**Interpretation Evolution:**

**Rising:** "Can we cover payroll?"
- Basic viability test
- Low expectations acceptable
- Focus: Build baseline

**Striving:** "Are we getting more efficient per person?"
- Productivity improvements tracked
- Systems creating leverage
- Focus: Efficiency without burnout

**Thriving:** "Can we predict the impact of our next hire?"
- Hiring ROI quantifiable
- Capacity modeling sophisticated
- Focus: Maintain efficiency at scale

**Driving:** "Have we hit optimal leverage?"
- Plateau acceptable
- Further gains require different levers
- Focus: Sustain without extraction

---

## Forecasting & Pipeline KPIs: Evolution by Stage

### Forecast Accuracy

| Stage | Accuracy Target | Time Horizon | Purpose | Update Frequency |
|-------|----------------|--------------|---------|------------------|
| **Rising** | ±40% (or not tracked) | 30 days | Cash visibility | Ad hoc |
| **Striving** | ±30% | 90 days | Basic planning | Monthly |
| **Thriving** | ±15-20% | 6 months | Capacity planning | Weekly |
| **Driving** | ±10% | 12 months | Strategic planning | Daily/weekly |

**Interpretation Evolution:**

**Rising:** "Will we make payroll next month?"
- Survival-focused
- Short time horizon
- High variance acceptable

**Striving:** "Can we plan 90 days ahead?"
- Hiring timeline planning
- Some confidence building
- Learning from variance

**Thriving:** "Can we confidently plan 6 months out?"
- Leadership leverage unlocking
- Resource coordination possible
- Variance analyzed systematically

**Driving:** "Can we model strategic scenarios?"
- Long-range planning confident
- Variance well-understood
- Optionality maximized

---

### Net MRR Movement

| Stage | Focus | Success Definition | Acceptable Performance | Growth Strategy |
|-------|-------|-------------------|------------------------|-----------------|
| **Rising** | Positive or flat | Not shrinking | Breaking even on MRR | Just retain what you win |
| **Striving** | Consistent positive | Growing steadily | +5-10% monthly | Retention + modest expansion |
| **Thriving** | Predictable growth | Compounding | +10-15% monthly | Systematic expansion |
| **Driving** | NRR >100% | Self-funding | +15-20%+ monthly | Expansion primary driver |

**Interpretation Evolution:**

**Rising:** "Are we replacing churn?"
- Net zero acceptable
- Just don't shrink
- Focus: Stop the bleeding

**Striving:** "Are we growing the base?"
- Positive momentum important
- Consistency matters
- Focus: Build growth rhythm

**Thriving:** "Is growth predictable?"
- Compounding visible
- Expansion systematic
- Focus: Make growth repeatable

**Driving:** "Is expansion driving growth?"
- New business supplemental
- Existing clients primary engine
- Focus: Maximize client LTV

---

## Client Retention & Account Health: Evolution by Stage

### Client Retention Rate

| Stage | Target | Mindset | Retention Strategy | When It's a Problem |
|-------|--------|---------|-------------------|---------------------|
| **Rising** | 75-85% | Learning to deliver consistently | Reactive firefighting | <70% |
| **Striving** | 85-90% | Systematic retention practices | Proactive account management | <80% |
| **Thriving** | 90-95% | Predictable retention engine | Strategic account planning | <88% |
| **Driving** | 92-98% | Enterprise-grade retention | Portfolio-level management | <90% |

**Interpretation Evolution:**

**Rising:** "Did we lose any important clients?"
- Count-based thinking
